1
00:00:04,693 --> 00:00:08,575
Why is Saraswatī Ṭhākur saying, 
“When you wake up in the morning,

2
00:00:08,575 --> 00:00:13,806
beat your mind with a broom 
a hundred times”?

3
00:00:14,515 --> 00:00:17,924
[Spiritual Jiu Jitsu]

4
00:00:18,416 --> 00:00:22,018
Thank God
we’re not our minds.

5
00:00:22,018 --> 00:00:24,818
[Laughing]

6
00:00:25,018 --> 00:00:31,262
The mind is like a mirror, 
an instrument of reflection.

7
00:00:31,570 --> 00:00:33,580
Have you ever been 
in a place where you saw

8
00:00:33,580 --> 00:00:37,062
a mirror covered with dust, 
and another layer of dust?

9
00:00:37,062 --> 00:00:42,065
What it means is: 
it gradually loses the quality of reflection,

10
00:00:42,065 --> 00:00:48,039
and starts giving 
a distorted view of yourself

11
00:00:48,071 --> 00:00:51,046
and everything else 
reflected before it.

12
00:00:51,046 --> 00:00:53,478
That’s the situation.

13
00:00:54,600 --> 00:01:00,270
Only when the layers of dust,
of misconception are removed, 
 

14
00:01:00,270 --> 00:01:02,526
then you can start 
gradually seeing

15
00:01:02,526 --> 00:01:06,470
yourself, others, 
the world … everything.

16
00:01:06,470 --> 00:01:14,666
And that’s exciting; a thrilling prospect; 
life changing.

17
00:01:15,052 --> 00:01:18,913
How can an ocean of ignorance,

18
00:01:18,929 --> 00:01:21,649
an insurmountable ocean of 
nescience or ignorance,

19
00:01:21,649 --> 00:01:24,794
be reduced to a drop?

20
00:01:25,976 --> 00:01:34,437
Sambandha-jñāna—a change of perspective, 
how we see things.

21
00:01:34,437 --> 00:01:37,750
So much so, Chakravartī Ṭhākur 
takes it to the extreme

22
00:01:37,750 --> 00:01:43,634
he’s saying, “Higher devotees, 
what will they think? Oh!”

23
00:01:43,742 --> 00:01:48,223
Because it says vatsa-padam, 
like the water left in the imprint

24
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:51,983
of the hoof of a calf: that small. 
He said,

25
00:01:51,983 --> 00:01:55,414
“But the devotee will think, 
‘Oh, but water that’s bathed …

26
00:01:55,414 --> 00:01:56,997
The cows are sacred and holy; 
 

27
00:01:56,997 --> 00:01:59,627
water that’s bathed the cow—
that’s very good.’”

28
00:01:59,627 --> 00:02:06,446
So even the so called ‘māyik’, 
there’s no more māya for them.

29
00:02:06,877 --> 00:02:16,380
For those in the highest position, 
everything’s favourable;

30
00:02:16,380 --> 00:02:20,261
“Every wave is favourable”, 
as Guru Mahārāj said.

31
00:02:20,261 --> 00:02:23,568
Babaji Mahārāj, when the children 
are throwing dirt claws at him

32
00:02:23,568 --> 00:02:26,180
and calling him ill names, 
he’s saying,

33
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:31,610
“I know it’s You, Kṛṣṇa, behind this, 
and I know how to deal with You also.

34
00:02:31,610 --> 00:02:39,958
I’ll tell Mother Yaśodā and she will spank you 
for your misbehaviour.”

35
00:02:40,282 --> 00:02:45,298
So we worship the lotus feet of 
Gaura Kiśor Dās Bābājī Mahārāj.

36
00:02:45,298 --> 00:02:46,207
Saraswatī Ṭhākur said,

37
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:51,837
“I found all spiritual knowledge
in a particle of his fingernail.”

38
00:02:53,047 --> 00:02:59,829
And to mimic him, to mimic a maha-bhāgavata, 
is an offence, and we will go down.

39
00:02:59,829 --> 00:03:06,180
But at least we get hope in knowing 
there are those who are like that,

40
00:03:06,257 --> 00:03:09,648
for whom everything 
is properly adjusted,

41
00:03:11,537 --> 00:03:15,228
and that religion 
means proper adjustment;

42
00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:18,100
under the influence of 
Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, and Vaiṣṇava,

43
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:21,404
we start seeing things differently.

44
00:03:21,945 --> 00:03:25,853
Guru Mahārāj 
would sometimes use jiu jitsu.

45
00:03:25,853 --> 00:03:31,364
What’s that negative
what’s coming towards you,

46
00:03:31,364 --> 00:03:40,631
to adjust it in such a way 
that it becomes a positive.

47
00:03:46,770 --> 00:03:54,188
So much misconception? 
Then preach proper conception; convert it.

48
00:03:54,552 --> 00:03:56,902
That’s what I like to say. 
So sometimes,

49
00:03:56,902 --> 00:04:05,740
if Marx or Lenin said, “Ratha Yātrā is the ultimate 
in religious expression”, “Yes!”

50
00:04:06,369 --> 00:04:10,142
Or Hegel, a brahmavādi, 
he’s saying things,

51
00:04:10,142 --> 00:04:15,185
someone else is saying things … 
we’ll see

52
00:04:15,416 --> 00:04:18,437
how it can make us 
think of Kṛṣṇa.

